race.description: J&L Cross Electrical & Air Conditioning Mdn Hcp
race.comment: SURPASSER (1) solid debut in stronger company when a handy fourth over 1150m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Gets map favours with the blinkers going on and looks hard to hold out. TOP SPEED (4) has mixed luck in two career starts. Pulled up with cardiac arrhythmia when a dismal fifth over 1100m at Nowra. Looking for this trip and further now. Improver who can overcome the awkward draw. TESORINO (12) returned from a let-up with a battling fourth over 1000m at Gosford. Fitter now and proven over this distance range. LUNE D'EXCELLENCE (3) tongue-tie goes on for this after disappointing at her last two starts on the provincial tracks. Andrew Gibbons sticks and look for a sharp improvement here.
